article.description: Adam Kunkel had 24 points as Belmont rolled past Kennesaw State 83-44 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Kunkel scores 24 to lift Belmont over Kennesaw State 83-44
article.linkText: Kunkel scores 24 to lift Belmont over Kennesaw State 83-44
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Adam Kunkel had 24 points as Belmont rolled past Kennesaw State 83-44 on Wednesday night. Tyler Scanlon had 12 points for Belmont (8-3), which earned its fourth straight win. Mitch Listau added 10 points and Michael Benkert had six rebounds. Tyler Hooker had 15 points and nine rebounds for the Owls (1-10). Belmont plays Alabama on Saturday. Kennesaw State matches up against Wofford at home on Sunday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
